  "metadata": {
    "what_it_measures": "Primary budget balance (total balance + interest payments) as a percent of GDP. Positive = primary deficit (spending > revenues excluding interest). Computed from FYFSD + FYOINT as share of nominal GDP.\n",
    "why_it_matters": "Primary deficit shows whether the government is adding to or subtracting from debt even before interest costs. A large primary deficit means the debt spiral is self-reinforcing regardless of interest rates.\n",
    "scoring_rule": ">5% \u2192 -40 | 3-5% \u2192 -20 | -3 to +3% \u2192 0 | <-3% \u2192 +30"
